<P><HI>Ignem autem aeternum</HI> non illis, <HI>quibus dicitur</HI> [<HI>discedite &agrave; me maledicti</HI>] <HI>paratum ostendit, sicut regnum justis, sed</HI> Diabolo, <HI>&amp; Angelis ejus: quia quantum adse, homines non ad perditionem creavit, sed ad vitam aeternam &amp; gaudium.</HI> (Note that <HI>Chry|sostome, Theophylact,</HI> and <HI>Euthymius,</HI> interpret those words of<NOTE PLACE="marg">Athanas. orat. de incarn. v<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1+ letters">rbi Dei. T. 1. p. 45.</NOTE> <HI>Christ,</HI> as <HI>Origen</HI> doth.)</P>
